# Session reports (not docs root)

QA, verification, E2E, and implementation-signoff reports are **session artifacts**. Write them
only under the active session folder.

## Required path

```
docs/sessions/{active_session.id}/reports/{report-name}.md
```

Equivalent: `{active_session.artifacts_dir}/reports/{report-name}.md`.

Resolve `active_session` via workflow-state-manager `read_context` before writing. If
`active_session` is null, **block** and route to **00-context** — do not fall back to `docs/`
root report paths.

## Report names by stage

| Stage | Report file |
|-------|-------------|
| 08-verify-build | `verification-report.md` |
| 09-qa | `qa-report.md` |
| 10-e2e | `e2e-report.md` |
| 11-verify-impl | `verify-impl.md` |

## Do not write (new work)

| Blocked path | Use instead |
|--------------|-------------|
| `docs/sessions/S000-internal-docs-archive/reports/qa-report.md` | `docs/sessions/{id}/reports/qa-report.md` |
| `docs/sessions/S000-internal-docs-archive/reports/verification-report.md` | `docs/sessions/{id}/reports/verification-report.md` |
| `docs/sessions/S000-internal-docs-archive/reports/e2e-report.md` | `docs/sessions/{id}/reports/e2e-report.md` |
| `docs/sessions/S000-internal-docs-archive/reports/implementation-verification.md` | `docs/sessions/{id}/reports/verify-impl.md` |

Pre-session reports archived under `docs/sessions/S000-internal-docs-archive/reports/` are
**historical read-only**. New QA, verification, E2E, and verify-impl reports **must** use
`docs/sessions/{id}/reports/`.

## Standing docs (still at docs root)

Long-lived specs remain at `docs/` root: `spec.md`, `feature-list.md`, `test-plan.md`,
`deploy-checklist.md`, `architecture.md`, bug reports under `docs/bug-reports/`, etc.

Agent/ops trackers live under `docs/sessions/S000-internal-docs-archive/` (execution plan,
deploy state, project board, historical root reports).

## State sync

On report write, workflow-state-manager `update` must set `stages.{key}.report` to the full
session path and append the same path to `artifacts[]` with `session_id`.

Reference: [sessions-reference.md](../skills/sessions-reference.md) §9–10.
